programme.title: Wild Guitar

Cult director Ray Dennis Steckler (The Thrill Killers) made his directorial debut with Wild Guitar, a cheesy, campy, surprisingly entertaining musical drama starring Arch Hall Jr. as Bud Eagle, a naïve singer who gets a shot at the big time. Steckler not only directed this frenzy of musical action, but also appears as a menacing thug working for record company crooks. Co-written and produced by Hall's father, Arch Hall Sr., (who should be known as the godfather of exploitation for films like The Chopper and The Sadist) this one really rocks!

programme.title: At War with the Army (1950)
programme.desc: It's Jerry Lewis and Dean Martin in their first staring vehicle! Lewis plays Alvin Korwin, a bumbler who goes from one disaster to the next, while the suave Sgt. Vic Puccinelli (Martin) tries to keep him out of trouble. Director Hal Walker, who had previously worked with the team of Bob Hope and Bing Crosby, found comedy gold in Martin and Lewis. Songs include 'You And Your Beautiful Eyes', and 'Tonda Wanda Hoy'. For trivia buffs, throughout the film, Lewis gives a Boy Scout salute instead of an Army salute.

programme.title: The Life of Christ - Vol. 1

programme.title: Let's Get Tough (1942)

Riled by the attack on Pearl Harbor, the boys (Leo Gorcey, Huntz Hall, and the rest) discover a real group of Japanese spies in their neighborhood. Are the East Siders bright enough to expose them? Sure they are! It’s good old American propaganda at its finest!

Holmes suspects a diabolical plot hatched by his arch enemy Moriarty, but the trail leads him to a society of hypnotists, and a mysterious woman. Is she a temptress of pleasure ­ or mistress of murder? Basil Rathbone and Nigel Bruce reprise their roles as Holmes and Dr. Watson, while Henry Daniell and Hillary Brooke are on hand as Moriarty and the alluring woman of the title!

programme.title: Invaders From Space
programme.desc: The evil salamander men have poisoned Earth with a plague, and it is up to Starman (Ken Utsui) to save mankind. But who are these salamander men, and why do they want to destroy us? It's hard to say, but you'll have fun watching them try.

programme.title: Broadway Jungle

programme.title: Curse of Bigfoot (1975)
programme.desc: Beware - not of Bigfoot, but of this movie! A group of high school kids go exploring in a cave and stumble upon a mummy, but when they remove it, the nasty old thing comes to life and starts terrorizing their small California town! If this doesn't look exactly like a 1970s movie, that's because producer/director Dave Flocker shot most of it in 1958 as Teenagers Battle the Thing. Bigfoot enthusiasts might be appalled, but lovers of schlock might find this feature to be just what they need!

programme.title: King of the Zombies
programme.desc: Blood­chilling revelations of the weird cult that practices its black magic in the impenetrable jungles of Central America! Dick Purcell, Joan Woodbury, Mantan Moreland, and Henry Victor star in this comedy chiller from Monogram, directed by Jean Yarbrough ( House of Horrors, The Brute Man). It’s all about a trio of plane crash survivors who take refuge in a mansion, where a sinister doctor is conducting zombie experiments. If you can sit through this spine­tingling carnival of shrieks and howls without getting the thrill of a lifetime...you must belong to the living dead!

programme.title: Creature from the Haunted Sea (1961)
programme.desc: Here’s another Roger Corman classic from the golden age of Drive-In schlock! In this spoof of horror and spy thrillers, American gangster Renzo Capetto (Anthony Carbone) decides to kill members of his bungling crew and blame their deaths on a legendary sea creature. What he doesn’t know is that the creature is actually out there!

programme.title: The Sadist
programme.desc: Written and directed by James Landis, this thriller loosely follows the story of the killing spree of Charles Starkweather (later films Badlands, 1973, and Natural Born Killers, 1994, were also based on Starkweather’s tale). Starring Arch Hall, Jr. The Sadist begins with three high school teachers driving through California. Unfortunately, their car breaks down in an abandoned area, where they experience a run in with a bloodthirsty sadist and his girlfriend. A truly terrifying experience, this film will have you on the edge of your seat from start to finish!

programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. Ted tames, trains and keeps Bess for himself, but after Ted is gravely injured in a fixed rodeo, Bess is stolen away from him and forced to join a cruel traveling carnival. This fast-paced western is from director Lew Landers (The Adventures of Rin Tin Tin).

Follow this tale of Dr. Christian as he matches wits with Professor Kenneth Parker, played by screen veteran Rod La Roque (The Ten Commandments). This drama features fine work from Oscar nominated director William C. McGann and a cast that that includes the great Frank Albertson (Psycho).

With a cast that includes Scott Brady, Rita Gamm, and Neville Brand, the story takes place on a remote army post where an artist romances a trio of women, just as a vengeful settler turns the army and the local Iroquois tribe against each other. Film buffs might like to know that the cinematography for this feature is by four time Oscar nominee Karl Struss, who won an Academy Award in 1929 for his work on Sunrise.

Secrets shroud Kathleen's demise, and soon there is a mysterious interloper prowling the grounds with a big axe to grind. Genuinely engaging and well-photographed, "Dementia 13" is a bone-chilling horror classic sure to thrill horror enthusiasts and Coppola fans alike.

programme.desc: As payment for solving a case, Holmes and Watson are invited to spend a weekend at an estate in the Balkans. Their vacation is cut short, however, when another guest, Prince Stefan, is poisoned.

programme.title: Death is a Red Balloon
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Al Brown Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: The New
programme.desc: A clerk named Stanley finds himself embroiled in the chaotic ongoings of New York City tourists inside an upscale hotel.

programme.title: Bud Takes Up the Dance
programme.desc: Bud prepares to take a girl to his first dance by learning dance steps from a 50 year old book.

programme.title: Speak Easily (1932)
programme.desc: The films Buster Keaton starred in at MGM during the 1930s are often dismissed as inferior to the work he did during the silent era, but the truth is that many of them are delightful. In Speak Easily he plays a shy professor who inherits some money, falls for a showgirl, and decides to become a Broadway producer. Jimmy Durante, and Hedda Hopper also star in this feature from director Edward Sedgwick, who happened to be behind some of Keaton’s best movies, including The Cameraman and Spite Marriage. This one might change your mind about the Keaton talkies!

programme.title: Springtime in the Sierras (1947)
programme.desc: Ads for this Roy Rogers classic roared HEAD FOR THE MUSICAL HILLS...ROY IS GUNNIN' FOR THRILLS! And thrills are what you'll get when you watch this fun, action packed B-Western from Republic Pictures. There's some great comic relief from Andy Devine and Chester Conklin, two of Hollywood's all-time greats. This old-fashioned shoot-'em-up was directed by William Witney, who would go on to direct many of television's top western sagas, including Bonanza, Wagon Train, and The Wild, Wild West.

programme.title: Abilene Town (1946)
programme.desc: Ablaze with guns and guts and glory! Randolph Scott headlines as a star studded cast in this yarn about battling homesteaders. Director Edwin L. Marin (Tall in the Saddle) spins this dramatic post-Civil War tale that takes place in the legendary cow town of Abilene, Kansas, coaxing fine performances from the likes of Ann Dvorak, Edgar Buchanan, Thonda Fleming, and Lloyd Bridges. Saddle up and hang on!

programme.title: Boy What a Girl (1947)
programme.desc: The scheming world of show business is the subject of this fascinating feature from Herald Pictures. Tim Moore, who went on to play “Kingfish” in the popular Amos & Andy show, heads a cast that includes Deek Watson and His Brown Dots, 'Big' Sid Catlett and his band, plus Ann Cornell and the International Jitterbugs. Also, look for legendary drummer Gene Krupa, who happened to visit the set, and was grabbed for a drumming cameo!

programme.title: Leather Burners
programme.desc: William Boyd plays Hopalong Cassidy who helps his friend find a herd of stolen cattle.

programme.title: The Gunman from Bodie (1941)
programme.desc: The Rough Riders, a popular group that thrilled audiences in the early 1940s, are after a gang of rustlers in this B-western from Hollywood's Poverty Row. Starring Buck Jones, Tim McCoy, and Raymond Hatton, this movie features everything from lawmen going undercover to the Rough Riders looking after an orphaned baby! Also, be on the lookout for the beautiful Christine McIntyre, who would go on to appear in several of the Three Stooges shorts for Colombia Pictures.

programme.title: God's Stepchildren (1938)
programme.desc: This controversial and still widely-discussed film produced, written and directed by prolific black filmmaker Oscar Micheaux (Body and Soul) centers on a young, light-skinned African American woman who struggles to find her place in both the black and white worlds. Groundbreaking for its time, and often cited as one of the most important movies about race of all time, it's little wonder why Time's Richard Corliss calls Micheaux "the D.W. Griffith of race cinema."

programme.title: Teenagers from Outer Space (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: A teenager falls in love with a young alien. Together, they must stop the alien's race from destroying the human race.

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: They Came From Beyond Space
programme.desc: Elvira presents the 1967 Sci-Fi classic They Came Beyond Space.

programme.title: Sisters of Death
programme.desc: During a sorority reunion, five women are stalked by a man seeking vengeance for the death of his daughter seven years ago.

programme.title: The Black Raven
programme.desc: This murder mystery occurs over one night at the Black Raven, an American hotel near the Canadian border. Mr. Amos Bradford is the proprietor, and runs the hotel with his assistant Andy. A group of strangers, guest at the hotel, are thrust together and must contend with two murders and $50,000 in stolen money.

programme.title: Spooks Run Wild
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi and the East Side Kids team up in this crazy comedy from Monogram Pictures. Leo Gorcey, Huntz Hall, Sunshine Sammy Morrison and the rest of the gang find themselves at a spooky mansion owned by the mysterious Nardo (Lugosi). Things get weird when the boys see one of their pals walking around in a trance. Did Nardo turn him into a zombie? Watch and find out!

programme.title: Devil's Daughter
programme.desc: Sylvia Walton returns from Harlem to take over a Jamaican plantation from her vindictive half-sister, amid the growing sound of drums.

programme.title: Scared To Death
programme.desc: The only color film to star Bela Lugosi was this mystery thriller from director Christy Cabanne (The Mummy’s Hand) made for the short­lived Golden Gate Pictures during the early months of 1946. Lugosi plays Professor Leonide, a cagy character who may have had something to do with the death of a young woman (who happens to be telling her tale from a slab at the morgue!). George Zucco, Molly Lamont, and Joyce Compton also star, as well as Angelo Rossitto, (Freaks) as a menacing dwarf with a habit of stepping on Lugosi’s foot!

programme.title: The Bat (1959)
programme.desc: Vincent Price stars in this thriller about a down­trodden country estate that becomes the site of a horrific murder. Prolific writer/director Crane Wilbur (He Walked by Night, Crime Wave) helms this feature, with a cast that includes Agnes Moorehead, Gavin Gordon, and in her last film role, Darla Hood of the Our Gang comedies. But which of them is the mysterious killer known as “The Bat”? You’ll find out soon enough. But beware – the scream you hear may be your own!

programme.title: Robin Hood of the Pecos (1941)
programme.desc: Roy Rogers finds himself elected sheriff in a wild Texas town after the Civil War. But can Roy handle a place under martial law? And can he save Gabby Hayes from being executed? And how many songs will he get to sing? Clear the burrs from your saddle and get ready for a good one, also starring Marjorie Reynolds, plus Sally Payne as Belle Starr, Queen of the Oklahoma Outlaws!

From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: Meet Clean Green Certified Founder Chris Van Hook
programme.desc: Certification for sustainable, naturally-grown agriculture, Clean Green Certified is the closest to “Organic” that the cannabiz can get. We're honored to welcome founder Chris Van Hook. Together, we explore the value of certification for industry operators, consumers and the planet. Chris offers tips and tricks that you can put to use in your own garden. Dig in! Founded in 2004, Swami Select has had the pleasure of being Clean Green Certified since 2011.

programme.title: Meet the International Canna Farmer's Association Chair, Kristin Nevedal
programme.desc: We're honored to welcome to today's show, Kristin Nevedal, International Cannabis Farmer's Association Chair. The International Cannabis Farmer’s Association strives to empower traditional Cannabis farmers through education, research and advocacy. Their programs raise public awareness about the benefits of traditionally farmed Cannabis and provide educational resources for farmers, regulators, industry and consumers. They advocate for the development of responsible regulations in CA, which are seen as crucially important due to the state’s significance to national and international policy development. They will promote public policy that ensures an equal share of licenses are issued to traditional sun grown Cannabis farmers. They conduct research to quantify the ecological superiority of traditionally farmed Cannabis as well as gathering data necessary to establish internationally recognized appellations of origin. They create a dynamic and creative consumer direct educational campaign that highlights the quality and ecological superiority of traditionally farmed sun grown Cannabis.

programme.title: What's It Like to Judge The Emerald Cup - Go Backstage with Swami Select
programme.desc: Founded in 2003, Northern California’s Emerald Cup advances the concept of sustainable, outdoor farming of medical cannabis. Longtime advocates of the spiritually and physically healing potential of regeneratively-grown cannabis, Swami Select founders Nikki Lastreto and Swami Chaitanya have judged The Emerald Cup’s flower competition since the event began. As the largest, organic, outdoor, medicinal cannabis competition in the world, The Cup advances our movement by cross-pollinating cultivators, patients and patrons with scientific and agriculture experts who work across industries. Now a global movement, the community celebration honors the year’s best, sun-grown, medicinal cannabis producers.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor & Comedian Aries Spear
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor comedian Aries Spears. From TV to film, actor Aries Spears spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about recent issues with Mike Epps and a social media post about black on black crime versus police racism against blacks.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Actor Miguel A. Nunez
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is actor Miguel Nunez. From TV to film, actor Miguel Nunez spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his career, life as a black actor and discuss some of the issues of today.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Alonzo Bodden
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is standup comedian and former “Last Comic Standing” champion Alonzo Bodden. DL and Alonzo discuss the issues of the pandemic and working as entertainers. They also discuss politics, racism, and other issues in the black community.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Ben Crump
programme.desc: DL Hughley Uncut on GFNTV. Guest on DL Uncut is Civil Rights Attorney Benjamin Crump. Attorney Crump is best known for taking on the toughest cases with national civil rights implications. From Trayvon Martin to Michael Brown, Crump continues to push the envelope for justice for those whose lives have been changed due an unfair legal system.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Charlamagne Tha God
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Uncut is one of the hosts on the nationally syndicated radio show The Breakfast Club – Charlamagne Tha God.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest David A. Arnold
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is stand-up comedian, writer and producer David Arnold. He has a special on Netflix called “Fat Ballerina”.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest DJ Doug E. Fresh
programme.desc: DL’s featured guest on DL Hughley Uncut is legendary DJ and Hip Hop pioneer Doug E. Fresh. Chris Spencer, the creator of the Real Husbands of Hollywood spends some time with DL and Jasmine to talk about his recent projects and working during a pandemic.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Erika Alexander
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is the brilliant actress from “The Cosby Show” and the 90’s hit series “Living Single” – Erika Alexander. Erika is a producer on the upcoming documentary “John Lewis: Good Trouble” which will release on July 3. DL, Jasmine, and Erika have a great discussion about the creating of “Living Single” and how the show “Friends” became a bigger hit after using the same concept. Erika gives great insight into racism in the entertainment industry.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Leonard Pitts
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is Pulitzer Prize Winner and columnist for the Miami Herald Leonard Pitts, Jr. Leonard Pitts has a progressive voice in journalism who dives deep into the racial and cultural issues of society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Matt Barnes
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former NBA star and 2017 NBA Champion Matt Barnes. Matt discusses his upbringing, thoughts on now legalized marijuana. Matt also gives his thoughts on George Floyd and the affects on our society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tamika Mallory
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Willy T Ribbs
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former race car driver Willy T. Ribbs. Willy was the first African American to test a Formula One racing car and first African American to compete in the Indy 500. DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: Stephanie McRae Ray Dejons Laffaholics Ep707
Ty Millz Hunter Ray Dejons Laffaholics Ep709
Warren Simpson Ray Dejons Laffaholics Ep701
Not Another Black Movie
programme.desc: Not Another Black Movie stars Damon Williams (Bad Boys of Comedy, Comic View, BET LIVE, The Tom Joyner Morning Show), Janet Hubert (The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air), Rodney Perry (The Monique Show, Who's Got Jokes) Jay Davis (Not Another Zombie Movie, Shots Fired), and Leon Rogers (WGCI, Comic View, Bad Boys of Comedy). - Not Another Black Movie is not only a spoof of a genre often associated with Tyler Perry films, but a satirical look at family dysfunction as well. Written by Jay Davis and Directed by Donte "Diesel" Williams, Not Another Black Movie addresses issues that effect many families whether they be rich or poor, black or white. Although we poke fun at some of the stereotypical roles portrayed in this genre, we hope to shed some light on problems that plague many families while giving you a good laugh.

programme.title: SpaceX CRS 23 Resupply
programme.desc: On Sun. Aug. 29, don’t miss the second launch attempt of a SpaceX Dragon spacecraft to the International Space Station. Live coverage of the mission begins at 2:45 a.m. EDT (06:45 UTC) with liftoff targeted for 3:14 a.m. EDT (07:14 UTC) from Launch Complex 39A at Kennedy Space Center in Florida. In addition to approximately 2,300 pounds (1,000 kilograms) of science experiments riding aboard the spacecraft, the crew can look forward to assortments of cheese, ice cream, and veggies! Docking to the orbiting lab is targeted for Mon., Aug. 30, at 11 a.m. EDT (15:00 UTC).

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Unfair Game
programme.desc: Zambia and Eswatini (formerly Swaziland) represent two divergent strategies on environmentalism. Meet people from both countries and learn of the successes, failures, and sacrifices they experienced seeking environmental justice.

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba is a Caribbean Hotspot. The island is a combination of gorgeous landscapes and a unique way of life. Travel from the Guanahacabibes Peninsula to Guantanamo. In Havana, meet students that wonder about their future prospects: exile or revolution?

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Disney Cruise Line
programme.desc: When Disney launched its first ship in 1998, The Disney Magic, it was unlike any other. Painted black to mimic classic ships from the age of cruising, the ship was decked out like only Disney could muster. Disney then bought an island in the Bahamas to serve as a destination for cruise guests only.

programme.title: The Old World Connection
programme.desc: A long, mountainous passage connects North and South America. Here, hundreds of thousands of species live in one of the richest and most diverse places on earth the Caribbean rainforests.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: From Peru to Tanzania
programme.desc: There are places on Earth worthy of absolute preservation and protection for all future generations. Meet people from Puerto Rico, Maryland, Peru, Tanzania, Slovakia, and Cambodia who all share an abiding belief in a sacred, healthy Earth.

programme.title: Sea Change
programme.desc: Fresh water is one of Earth’s sacred resources. Lake Turkana’s freshwater resources are vital to countless people who rely on it for sustenance. When a dam threatened to disturb the Lake’s ecosystem, some took action to protect their home.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: The Route of the Two Oceans
programme.desc: The thin ridge that links the two Americas is a miniature world unto itself and concentrates a vast amount of diversity into a small area of land. Follow the Inter-American Highway from Panama City to the Isthmus of Rivas in Nicaragua, the narrowest ridge of Central America.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Disney Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Explore the process of designing and creating Disney’s Animal Kingdom with incredible behind-the-scenes footage. Discover how Disney incorporates live animals into their attractions and uncover the time taken to create authentic habitats that allow visitors to experience a safari or jungle trek.

programme.title: Forests Between Two Worlds
programme.desc: At the edge of the Old World there is a peninsula connecting Europe and Africa. With warm sheltering tropics in its southern regions and a mountainous north of wet and old forests, the Iberian Peninsula contains mystery and diversity.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: S7E10 - Venice: City of Dreams
programme.desc: In Venice, we'll sample the splendor of the Doge's Palace, St. Mark's Basilica, Grand Canal, and masterpieces from the Venetian Renaissance — then take a glide on a gondola.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Kyushu
programme.desc: Explore the island of Kyushu with it's dramatic landscape and hot sands, and discover the essence of Japanese cuisine with Daisuke Utagawa and Rudy Maxa.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Tokyo
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take us to the heart of Japan in Tokyo where culinary geniuses strive for perfection as they prepare everything from sushi to the wasabi.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Hokkaido
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take you to Japan's northern frontier Hokkaido. The hot spring capital of Japan with its many volcanoes, Hokkaido also boosts some of the world greatest ramen, ramen noodles, and legendary whiskey.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 1
programme.desc: Host Rudy Maxa and Washington, D.C. restaurateur and chef Daisuke Utagawa enthusiastically eat their way through Hong Kong, from cheap but authentic, hole-in-the-wall Chinese restaurants to Michelin-starred palaces. Along the way they illustrate the excitement and energy that defines Hong Kong.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 2
programme.desc: Dramatic photography by renowned shooters Karel Bauer and Joe Pontecorvo bring Hong Kong into viewers' homes as never before. Stray from the iconic photo of Hong Kong as a wall of skyscrapers against Victoria Peak with the city's harbor in a foreground and visits the other side of the island.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Washington, DC, restaurateur Daisuke Utagawa and travel journalist Rudy Max deliver viewers directly to Bangkok’s sprawling city temples, its huge flower market, its vibrant klongs (canals), and to its most interesting cuisine, all of which made Bangkok the world’s most-visited city by travelers.

programme.title: From Guatemala to the Congo
programme.desc: Stewardship of the land is a central part of the human condition. Unfortunately, in some cases, so is greed. Meet people from California, Congo, India, Australia, Guatemala, and Slovenia whose spirit matches their intent to live healthily.

programme.title: From Chicago to the Karoo
programme.desc: A healthy mind, body, and environment are all critical for living happy and productive lives. Meet pioneering people in Iraq, Colombia, South Africa, Indonesia, the United States, and Italy who believe in living symbiotically with nature.

programme.title: The Mohawk Trail Across New England
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America’s richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: The Iron Curtain Trail
programme.desc: For almost half a century, Europe was demonstrably divided into East and West by the "Iron Curtain,” an imaginary, yet strongly re-enforced, barrier separating Europe that stretched between the Barents and Black Seas. For 40 years, the Iron Curtain was a potent symbol of division between people.

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Walt Disney Resort Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Since 1971, Walt Disney World has grown from a theme park and three hotels in Orlando, Florida to a vacation resort of unprecedented size and scope. Today the property encompasses four major theme parks, three water parks, 29 resort hotels, 99 holes of golf, two miniature golf courses, and more.

programme.title: The Great Bridge
programme.desc: Central America is a strip of land connecting two large land masses, a small region with an extraordinary natural richness. The Iberian Peninsula is the most bio-diverse region in Europe, acting as an umbilical cord between Africa and Europe. Both places are defined as "biological bridges."

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: St. Augustine
programme.desc: First, we will take a sip from the distinctively tasting Fountain of Youth. Then we will touch the coquina walls of the undefeated Castillo San Marcos. Next, separate pirate truth from pirate myth at the appropriately named, Pirate Museum, and cure what ails us at the oldest General Store.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Los Angeles, My Own Heart of Darkness
programme.desc: Los Angeles, CA: New York chef, Anthony Bourdain, descends into the culinary underbelly of his metropolitan nemesis, Los Angeles, where he experiences the trials of celebrity fame and the joys of West Coast cuisine.

programme.title: The French Laundry Experience
programme.desc: Napa, CA: Marooned in San Francisco, Tony tastes local shellfish and durian ice cream before embarking on a pilgrimage to experience the genius of Thomas Keller, chef and owner of The French Laundry.

programme.title: France's Normandy
programme.desc: From a dramatic coast to rural pastures, this sweet section of France abounds with apple orchards, enchanting villages, stunning abbeys, and sparkling seaports. We base in the lovely seaside town Honfleur. At Giverny, and in the museums in Rouen and Honfleur, we discover the birth of Impressionism.

programme.title: Medieval Europe
programme.desc: The medieval world is one of the big draws of European Travel. Moody ruins, "tippy" towers, cobbled streets, sparkling mosaics, monasteries, castles, and cathedrals form the core of many a tourist's dreams. In this episode, we make sense out of a fascinating 1,000 years of history.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.desc: When a person dies, or to celebrate a harvest or important visit, the Baining tribesmen create masks representing the Spirit of the Forest. A great fire is then lit in the village, and dancers adorning the masks dance around the fire, jumping on the embers to prove they are stronger than the flames.

programme.title: Peru: Masters of Chaos
programme.desc: Anthropologist Anne-Sylvie Malbrancke journeys to meet Jenny, a young Peruvian who has crossed the country to ask the sacred lakes to heal her medical issue. For more than 700 years, shamans have drawn their power to heal from the Huaringas, sacred lagoons located on the border of Peru and Ecuador.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. programme.title: Wonders of America's National Parks

Products of fire and ice, wind, water, and time, together we will explore the extraordinary wonders of America’s National Parks that elevate the spirit and humble the soul.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Late to the Party: Dall's Sheep
programme.desc: Greg and Karl search for a late-season Dall Sheep. Short days, long nights, and uncertainty as to whether the rams are moving into their winter range all hang over the hunters as they watch the clock tick down on the season.

programme.title: Shankfest 5 Part 1
programme.desc: It's Shankfest 5, and Group 1 is up to bat at the Choctaw Hunting Lodge in Oklahoma. So many pigs, so little time

programme.title: Timberghost Ranch Iowa
programme.desc: Despite 50 years of hunting experience, Larry Weishuhn can still be the victim of the dreaded buck fever. Larry is hunting at Timberghost Ranch in Iowa, where the buck of a lifetime waits... if he can hit it.

programme.title: Lonestar Outfitters Texas
programme.desc: Larry Weishuhn – aka Mr. Whitetail – passes on the torch to the next generation of hunters as he chases deer with his two grandsons near San Antonio, Texas. Don’t let their young age fool you, for Jake and Joshua are seasoned hunters who know what it takes to get a mature buck on the ground.

programme.title: Show Me The Bulls
programme.desc: CJ Buck, President and CEO of Buck Knives, and former Indy car driver Johnny Unser, Jr. take on Idaho in archery season, while Cameron Hanes looks to connect in Colorado.

programme.title: Wild Wild West
programme.desc: Bone Collector and Realtree's Spring Thunder hit Wyoming, South Dakota, and Montana all in one nonstop turkey killin show!

programme.title: Heart Of Dixie
programme.desc: Michael Waddell chasing hard headed Easterns in his home state of Georgia

programme.title: A Mayan Fowl Play
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey and good friend Francisco Bergaz travel into the thick jungles of the Yucatan Peninsula to hunt the gorgeous ocellated turkey.

programme.title: Patagonia Wild
programme.desc: Chris Dorsey and his brother Joe visit Argentina to experience an outdoorsman's paradise. Stag, hog, and quail are on the itinerary in this Southern Hemisphere adventure.

programme.title: Hot and Hevi
programme.desc: It’s the Wisconsin Waterfowl Opener & Pickett dominates an upland hunt in the afternoon.

programme.title: Risks and Trepidations
programme.desc: Fourteen days into their race, with their energy reserves drained and food rations diminished, the brigade is on a mission to find new ways of conserving energy, supplementing their diet, and keeping morale up. Their whitewater skills are put to the test as they navigate a series of intense downstream rapids in their 29 foot 2500 lbs voyageur canoe, following the ebbs and flows of the Hayes River, as it twists and turns across the northeastern stretches of Manitoba. Faced with a dilemma to go fast or err on the side of caution, the group is divided and tensions come to a head, but it’s Wanda that suffers the biggest blow.

programme.title: A Traditional Catfish and Turtle Hunt
programme.desc: Jim heads down south to do a little traditional catfish and turtle hunting with some of the best of the best.

programme.title: Broadway Bucks Part 2
programme.desc: As rifle season continues, Tom goes the extra mile to ensure a one hundred percent success rate.

programme.title: The Spoils of Decoying Whitetails
programme.desc: Longtime Bowhunter Magazine Contributor Danny Farris decoys rutting Illinois bucks at eye level.

programme.title: Panhandlin' for a Buck!
programme.desc: Gordon Whittington is headed to the Panhandle of Texas to hunt with T-Fork Outfitters, Dr. Kroll talks warm season food plots, Laden Force discusses Sig's new BDX system and Jeremy Moore kicks off a three part series on shed dogs.

programme.title: Old-School Deer Hunt, Part 1
programme.desc: Mike and friends hunt deer and hogs at Gopher Plantation, a replica of a South Georgia farm as existed at the turn of the 19th century.

programme.title: Trout Help
programme.desc: Chef Scott Leysath is home in his kitchen for this one, and he’s got a bunch of Trout to cook. Today’s guests feature Susie Jimenez, Tommy Gomes, Stacy Lyn Harris, Brad Fenson, Cee Dub, and Buddy T.

programme.title: The Reluctant Bull Rider
programme.desc: Derek joins Hall-of-Famer Gary Leffew at his first-class bull riding school.

programme.title: New Smyrna Beach Redfish
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Mike Rathjen for some incredible redfish action in the Ponce Inlet. They find monster redfish schooled up and biting great.

programme.title: Offshore Gulf Grouper
programme.desc: Show host, Jason South joins Capt. Seth Hayes for some incredible offshore gag grouper action off the coast of Ft.Myers.

programme.title: Bad Mood
programme.desc: Bou and Rob fish clients in the Cheeca Lodge & Spa Tarpon Invitational. They battle through wind and rain in this, the first tournament of the tarpon season.

programme.title: Golden Fly Part 2
programme.desc: It’s Day 2 of the Golden Fly Tarpon Tournament in Islamorada, FL. Rob is fishing tournament champion Andy Mill and Bou is fishing his friend Paul Nute.

programme.title: Beautiful Danger
programme.desc: Epic adventure awaits at the Dry Tortugas, but fishing off the grid is no easy task. As the SFTV crew discovers, preparation is everything.

programme.title: Young Salt, Old Spirit
programme.desc: Armed with the skills of generations past, rough and tumble New Englanders teach the SFTV crew how to catch the region's sporty summertime species.

programme.title: Atlantic Gladiators
programme.desc: New England pelagics like swordfish and bluefin tuna bring more than sport. It's a heavyweight, high octane battle, and the angler is the underdog.

programme.title: Beachfront
programme.desc: Tarpon are caught right out in front of Panama City Beach condos. Justin and a friend give visitors a front row seat to the silver king’s spectacular aerial dance.

programme.title: Jacks Be Roiling
programme.desc: When word gets out that Jack Crevalle are in a feeding frenzy, Justin and fellow Captain Kyle Pitts speed down the Intracoastal Waterway to find them doing just that.

programme.title: Trolling Up Musky
programme.desc: Fall trolling for muskies on Lake of the Woods in northwest Ontario. Maintain large lures in the fish zone

programme.title: Vermillion Walleye
programme.desc: Walleye fishing on Lake Vermilion in northern Minnesota. Jigging Rapalas are classic ice fishing lures applied to open water

programme.title: Bass In The Shadows
programme.desc: Fishing (Rapala’s Shadow Rap Shad) for largemouths, smallmouths and walleyes! Its dying baitfish action is irresistible

programme.title: Ford Frontier Fishing
programme.desc: Immersion into life is most important for those who have faced death. For the warrior who has experienced the crucible of combat and paid a steep price for our freedom, the chance to be set free on wild waters is the chance to recognize the sweetness of life and the bonds of friendship. Flip Pallot and retired U.S. Army Ranger, CPT Chad Fleming, fish the wilds of Alaska on this episode of Ford's Fishing Frontiers.

programme.title: Incoming
programme.desc: Some of the best musky fishing occurs with an impending storm. To make the most of these conditions, you often need to work as a team to determine the hot baits and fish fast covering water to maximize the number of bites you can get throughout the day. Jim Saric and Musky Hunter Field Editor Bob Turgeon discuss strategies for making the most of the situation when the bite is on.

programme.title: Biometrics
programme.desc: Biometrics are all of the factors that impact a musky’s activity level. Jim Saric and Jeff Lang from Blue Sky Invention Company discuss the Musky Hunter Television app and how it uses biometrics to predict musky activity and take your musky catches to an entirely new level!

programme.title: Andrew Airways 1
programme.desc: Alaska’s weather rules bush flying. When it’s in, your stranded; when it’s coming, you’re pushing to get out. Stuck with a tight flight schedule on Afognak Island, Larry, Audrey, and the crew are left with only one hour to fish before their weather-escaping flight. But it’s amazing what one hour can catch..

programme.title: Andrew Airways 2
programme.desc: Join Larry Csonka, Audrey Bradshaw, and SmokeeJo, as they wrap up their stay in the Kodiak Islands with even more silvers. But they aren’t the only ones on the streams... the bears are also taking advantage of the shallow water chock-full of coho.

programme.title: Squirrel Masters

programme.title: Astypalea: Smart, Sustainable Island
programme.desc: Astypalea up until now is probably only known to insiders. The small island is located in the Aegean Sea, it belongs to Greece and is especially known for its butterflies. This is likely to change in the future: Astypalea will become a model for smart, emission-free mobility. The island wants to prove that a purely electric transport system is already possible today – without any restrictions on the mobility of its inhabitants. We explain the details.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. programme.title: Political Animals
programme.desc: Political Animals celebrates the legendary civil rights victories of four trailblazing California state politicians: Carole Migden, Sheila Keuhl, Jackie Goldberg, and Christine Kehoe. Fierce and unrelenting, these courageous women toppled a partisan majority and emerged victors to pass historic legislation for social justice and LGBT+ equality. It was a hard fight – filled with vehemently heated debates and hateful insults hurled by opponents. Today, the message behind Political Animals is more important than ever as the current political theatre unfurls around the globe. These inspiring biographies further reveal the critical importance for public resistance at the local level to pressure lawmakers to enact difficult change. Political Animals is a clear call to action for a new era of greater democratic participation. We invite you to follow in the footsteps of these historic leaders and become the next pioneering political animal!

programme.title: Why Can't I Be Me? Around You
programme.desc: Rusty Tidenberg, drag-racing aficionado, shocked friends and family by coming out as trans. programme.title: TransMilitary
programme.desc: The 2018 SXSW Audience Award-winning feature film debut by Gabriel Silverman, Fiona Dawson, & Jamie Coughlin, TransMilitary follows the Emmy-nominated short film Transgender, at War and in Love. Around 15,500 transgender people serve in the U.S. military (notably the largest transgender employer in the U.S.), where they must conceal their gender identity because military policies ban their service. TransMilitary chronicles the lives of four individuals (Senior Airman Logan Ireland, Corporal Laila Villanueva, Captain Jennifer Peace & First Lieutenant El Cook) defending their country’s freedom while fighting for their own. They put their careers and their families’ livelihoods on the line by coming out as transgender to top brass officials in the Pentagon in hopes of attaining the equal right to serve. The ban was lifted in 2016, but with President Trump now trying to reinstate it, their futures hang in the balance once again.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.title: For My Wife

programme.title: Kumu Hina
programme.desc: Imagine a world where a little boy can grow up to be the woman of his dreams, and a young girl can rise to become a leader among men. Welcome to Kumu Hina's Hawai'i. Kumu Hina tells the inspiring story of Hina Wong-Kalu, a transgender native Hawaiian teacher, or kumu, who brings to life Hawai‘i's traditional embrace of mahu - those who embody both male and female spirit. Produced by Emmy-winning directors Dean Hamer and Joe Wilson in association with ITVS and Pacifc Islanders in Communications, the film traces Hina's evolution from Collin Wong, a timid high school boy, to her present position as a married woman and cultural director of a school in one of Honolulu's grittier neighborhoods. When Ho‘onani, a charismatic 6th grade girl, asks to join the school's all-male hula troupe, Kumu Hina gives her the opportunity to express her inner male spirit. As teacher and student prepare for a climactic end-of-year public performance, they meet many obstacles, but hold fast to the idea that being true to oneself matters most.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: Jakub Jozef Orlinski- Il Pomo D'Oro
programme.desc: Il controtenore polacco Jakub Józef Orlinski si è guadagnato in breve tempo la reputazione di cantante dalla sorprendente padronanza vocale e dall'audacia scenica. Questo concerto riflette la tanto attesa uscita del suo primo album, Anima Sacra, un recital di arie sacre del XVIII secolo recentemente riscoperte con il gruppo barocco Il Pomo d'oro.

programme.title: Leonidas Kavakos And Yuja Wang
programme.desc: Due degli artisti più emblematici del Festival di Verbier interpretano insieme le opere di Brahms in un ricco concerto di musica da camera. Acclamato all'unanimità dal mondo della musica classica dal 1985, quando fece scalpore diventando il più giovane vincitore del prestigioso Concorso Sibelius, il violinista greco Leonidas Kavakos combina in questo concerto il suo virtuosismo con quello della pianista Yuja Wang, un'artista affermata a soli 26 anni.

programme.title: W. A. Mozart: Piano Concerto No.19

Un'opera magistrale, composta per la cerimonia di incoronazione dell'imperatore austriaco Leopoldo II nel 1790.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Piano Recital
programme.desc: La scelta di Lang Lang per la musica e la modalità di presentazione ha affermato la sua sensibilità del XXI° secolo rendendo al tempo stesso omaggio ai suoi precedenti pianistici e ai suoi mentori. Non è stato certo un caso che abbia suonato Wanderer Fantasy di Schubert, la prima opera che il suo insegnante del Curtis Institute, Gary Graffman, aveva registrato e usato per concludere il concerto delle Réminiscences Du Don Juan de Mozart di Liszt, associato ai più grandi virtuosi del pianoforte.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Bach and Philippe Herreweghe
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe, direttore d'orchestra e del coro belga, è specializzato in musica antica, in particolare quella di Johann Sebastian Bach. Qui dirige il Collegium Vocal de Gand, che ha fondato nel 1970. A Parigi, nella chiesa barocca di Saint-Roch, le sontuose voci di Grace Davidson (soprano), Damien Guillon (controtenore), Thomas Hobbs (tenore) e Peter Kooij (basso) risuonano in un programma religioso dedicato al Natale.

programme.title: Paolo Arrivabeni - ORW
programme.desc: L'opera è sinonimo di cantanti. Eppure l'orchestra sinfonica gioca un ruolo cruciale in queste opere musicali e teatrali. L'Orchestre Royal de Wallonie - Liège, sotto la direzione di Paolo Arrivabeni, ci introduce quindi alla ricchezza della musica strumentale di alcune opere.

programme.title: PUCCINI by Julien Lestel Company
programme.desc: Le eroine del compositore Giacomo Puccini erano quasi sempre condannate a un tragico destino. Qui vengono portate sul palco accompagnate dalle arie più belle. Questa coreografia è un omaggio all'opera, e in particolare all'illustre compositore scomparso.

programme.desc: Quincy Jones mostra la ricchezza della performance classica in tutta la sua gloria e la rende accessibile a tutti. Vivi la potenza e la bellezza dei migliori concerti, opera e danza.

programme.title: Ivan Fischer: Schubert and Bruckner
programme.desc: Sotto la direzione magistrale di Iván Fischer, l'orchestra esegue due opere incompiute del periodo romantico. Questo intenso programma, eseguito con sentimento e profondità dalla Budapest Festival Orchestra, ci immerge immediatamente in un abisso emotivo.

programme.title: Daniel Barenboim - W. E. Orchestra
programme.desc: Orchestra di portata molto simbolica, la West-Eastern Divan Orchestra è stata creata grazie allo slancio del direttore israelo-argentino Daniel Barenboim e del critico letterario Edward Saïd. Riunisce tutti i giovani musicisti israeliani e dei paesi arabi vicini - come ad esempio la Siria, la Giordania o i territori palestinesi - con un unico obiettivo: gettare dei ponti fra le comunità attraverso la musica. In diretta dalla Philharmonie di Berlino nel 2006, interpretano l’imponente nona sinfonia di Beethoven.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Piano Recital
programme.desc: La scelta di Lang Lang per la musica e la modalità di presentazione ha affermato la sua sensibilità del XXI° secolo rendendo al tempo stesso omaggio ai suoi precedenti pianistici e ai suoi mentori. Non è stato certo un caso che abbia suonato Wanderer Fantasy di Schubert, la prima opera che il suo insegnante del Curtis Institute, Gary Graffman, aveva registrato e usato per concludere il concerto delle Réminiscences Du Don Juan de Mozart di Liszt, associato ai più grandi virtuosi del pianoforte.

programme.title: The Magic Flute - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Il Flauto magico è l'opera finale di Mozart. Un racconto meraviglioso, una favola popolare o un racconto che marca il periodo della sua maturità, la storia della regina della notte, il principe Tamino, il vanaglorioso uccellatore Papageno e il suo flauto magico, ha lasciato il segno nei cuori e nelle menti. Accompagnato dalla prestigiosa Berliner Philharmoniker Orchestra sotto alla direzione di Simon Rattle, il direttore Robert Carsen rivisita questo classico con un tocco raffinato attraverso una profonda riflessione sulla vita e sulla morte.

programme.title: W. A. Mozart: Piano Concerto No.19
programme.desc: Qui il grande pianista Radu Lupu esegue il Concerto n. 19 in FA maggiore di Mozart, accompagnato dall'orchestra della Deutsche Kammerphilharmonie sotto alla direzione di David Zinman. Un'opera magistrale, composta per la cerimonia di incoronazione dell'imperatore austriaco Leopoldo II nel 1790.

programme.title: Vox Luminis: Handel in Versailles
programme.desc: È nella sontuosa Cappella Reale di Versailles che il gruppo Vox Luminis porta Georg Friedrich Handel sotto i riflettori. Specializzato nel repertorio barocco inglese, italiano e tedesco, il gruppo Vox Luminis, sotto la direzione di Lionel Meunier, esegue con leggerezza e raffinatezza due salmi, un'opera lirica e un oratorio.

programme.title: Danza Contemporánea de Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba non è solo famosa per i suoi sigari, ma anche per la sua vita culturale molto ricca - dove la danza gioca un ruolo importante. Nel film di Patrick Lauze, la compagnia Danza - Contemporánea de Cuba, creata nel 1959, esegue tre danze sacre al Teatro Nazionale Alicia Alonso all'Avana, Cuba.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
programme.desc: L'affascinante soprano spagnolo Saioa Hernández, con la sua voce potente e ammaliante, interpreta le famose arie d'opera italiane in concerto. Questo spettacolo ci permette di apprezzare il bel canto "l'arte del canto lirico" utilizzato nelle opere dal XVII secolo. Valorizzando le capacità tecniche dei cantanti, a volte a scapito dell'espressione scenica, la voce vola come fosse un uccellino.

programme.title: Beethoven - Daniel Barenboim
programme.desc: Qui l'illustre direttore d'orchestra Daniel Barenboim suona e dirige i cinque concerti di Beethoven con l'Orchestra della Staatskapelle di Berlino in occasione del suo 65° compleanno. Il Concerto n. 5 in MI bemolle maggiore, noto come "L'Imperatore", vede il maestro rivoluzionare la forma con un primo movimento lungo seicento battute. Un'improvvisazione messa per iscritto?

programme.title: Denis Matsuev at Concertgebouw
programme.desc: Il pianista russo Denis Matsuev, uno dei più grandi virtuosi del suo strumento, si esibisce qui in un recital solista sul palcoscenico del Concertgebouw di Amsterdam. In programma ci sono le Stagioni di Tchaikovsky, un classico della musica russa per celebrare il 175° compleanno del compositore nel 2015, e un'altra opera romantica: La Kreisleriana di Schumann. Egli esegue anche l'impressionante e virtuosistico "Tre Movimenti di Petrushka" di Stravinsky.

programme.title: G. Puccini: Tosca - Simon Rattle
programme.desc: Basata su un'opera teatrale di Victorien Sardou, l'opera Tosca ha conquistato il pubblico sin dalla sua uscita nel 1900. Questo dramma verista è sublimato dalla composizione virtuosa di Puccini. - Sotto la direzione di Sir Simon Rattle, la storia d'amore di Floria Tosca e Mario Cavaradossi si svolge e viene messa alla prova dal tirannico capo della polizia Scarpia, che governa Roma. In questa produzione, il famoso tenore argentino Marcelo Álvarez trascende la scena, accompagnato dalla sublime Kristine Opolais nel ruolo dell'eroina.

programme.title: Lang Lang - Debut at Carnegie Hall
programme.desc: Anche se Lang Lang aveva a malapena festeggiato il suo 21° compleanno all'epoca di questo concerto, il suo portfolio vanta già una serie impressionante di apparizioni internazionali di alto profilo. La sua selezione di apertura, le Variazioni "Abegg" di Schumann, figura nel debutto alla Carnegie Hall di Yevgeny Kissin nel 1990, mentre la sonata in DO maggiore di Haydn è apparsa due volte durante il celebre debutto dei cinque concerti di Sviatoslav Richter al Carnegie nel 1960.

programme.title: Bach and Philippe Herreweghe
programme.desc: Philippe Herreweghe, direttore d'orchestra e del coro belga, è specializzato in musica antica, in particolare quella di Johann Sebastian Bach. Qui dirige il Collegium Vocal de Gand, che ha fondato nel 1970. A Parigi, nella chiesa barocca di Saint-Roch, le sontuose voci di Grace Davidson (soprano), Damien Guillon (controtenore), Thomas Hobbs (tenore) e Peter Kooij (basso) risuonano in un programma religioso dedicato al Natale.

programme.title: Daniel Oren & Saioa Hernandez - ORW
